                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d392">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Vignaud</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received Feb. 25.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A decree of the minister of agriculture, gazetted this morning, forbids the
                    importation into France, until further orders, of cattle coming from the United
                    States. Cattle shipped before February 24 will be admitted under certain
                    restrictions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Vignaud</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chargé</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
